  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6567.53 sitting between the massive negative gamma wall at 6550 (-10.2B) and positive gamma resistance at 6600 (+6.4B), dealers are currently in buying mode as spot trades above the max negative gamma strike. The breakout regime confirms dealers are short gamma and will amplify moves—they'll aggressively buy any dip toward 6550/6560 and sell strength into 6600. Watch for volatile whipsaws in this 50-point range, with 6600 acting as critical resistance where dealer selling pressure intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect amplified moves with strong bounces off 6550 and heavy selling pressure into 6600.",
